beans.description:
ONDEX OWL Parser configuration for importing the Experimental Factor Ontology.
You can find details on the format of this file (and its imports) at: https://github.com/Rothamsted/ondex-knet-builder/wiki/%5BOWL-Parser%5D---Mapping-OWL-Ontologies-to-ONDEX

property.name: description
property.value: The Experimental Factor Ontology (EFO) provides a systematic description of many experimental variables available in EBI databases, and for external projects (https://www.ebi.ac.uk/efo/).

property.name: description
property.value: Provides a systematic description of many experimental variables available in EBI databases, and for external projects (https://www.ebi.ac.uk/efo/).

property.name: description
property.value: A top container for relations that were auto-computed from EFO.

property.name: description
property.value: A relation between an entity and a dependent continuant; the reciprocal relation of inheres_in [GOC:cjm] example of usage: red eye bearer_of redness. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.org/obo/owl/OBO_REL#bearer_of'.

property.name: description
property.value: A relationship between a disease and some feature of that disease, where the feature is either a phenotype or an isolated disease. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0004029'.

property.name: description
property.value: q inheres in part of w if and only if there exists some p such that q inheres in p and p part of w. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002314'.

property.name: description
property.value: Participates in is a primitive instance-level relation between a continuant and a process in which it participates. For example a scanner participates in a scanning process at some specific time. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://www.obofoundry.org/ro/ro.owl#participates_in'.

property.name: description
property.value: A relation between a continuant C and a role R. The reciprocal relation of role_of. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo#has_role'.

property.name: description
property.value: Has_participant is a primitive instance-level relation between a process, a continuant, and a time at which the A continuant participates in some way in the process. The relation obtains, for example, when this particular process of oxygen exchange across this particular alveolar membrane has_participant this particular sample of hemoglobin at this particular time. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://www.obofoundry.org/ro/ro.owl#has_participant'.

property.name: description
property.value: A relationship that holds between a biological entity and a phenotype. Here a phenotype is construed broadly as any kind of quality of an organism part, a collection of these qualities, or a change in quality or qualities (e.g. abnormally increased temperature). The subject of this relationship can be an organism (where the organism has the phenotype, i.e. the qualities inhere in parts of this organism), a genomic entity such as a gene or genotype (if modifications of the gene or the genotype causes the phenotype), or a condition such as a disease (such that if the condition inheres in an organism, then the organism has the phenotype). Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002200'.

property.name: description
property.value: S only_in_taxon T iff: S SubClassOf in_taxon only T. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002160'.

property.name: description
property.value: Relation between a process and a material fulfilling a role (i.e. realizing a role within the context of the process). For example a human realizing role of teacher within a lesson teching process. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000308'.

property.name: description
property.value: X distalmost_part_of Y <=> X is part_of Y and X is adjacent_to the distal boundary of Y. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BSPO_0001108'.

property.name: description
property.value: x composed_primarily_of y if and only if more than half of the mass of x is made from y or units of the same type as y. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002473'.

property.name: description
property.value: x proximal_to y iff x is closer to the point of attachment with the body than y. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BSPO_0000100'.

property.name: description
property.value: X in_lateral_side_of Y <=> if X is in_left_side_of Y or X is in_right_side_of Y. X is often, but not always a paired structure. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BSPO_0000126'.

property.name: description
property.value: Relation between a realizable entity and a process. Reciprocal relation of realizes. Mapped from the original URI: 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000300'.
